(Description)
A phrase is a palindrome if, after converting all uppercase letters into lowercase letters and removing all non-alphanumeric characters, 
it reads the same forward and backward. Alphanumeric characters include letters and numbers.

Given a string s, return true if it is a palindrome, or false otherwise.

--- Solution ---
class Solution {
    public boolean isPalindrome(String s) {
        s = s.toLowerCase().replaceAll("[^a-z0-9]", "");

        if (s.length() <= 1) {
            return true;
        }

        int left = 0;
        int right = s.length() - 1;

        while (left < right) {
            if (s.charAt(left) != s.charAt(right)) {
                return false;
            }

            left ++;
            right --;
        }

        return true;
    }
}

--- Approach ---
At first step, it deletes all non-alphanumeric characters, converting uppercase to lowercase.
Then, it set the left and right values, that they are first and last index of the converted string, s.

Second, while loop constantly compare each characters, left and right of the string s.
When they aren't same, it is not palindrome, returning false.
Otherwise, nothing returned the false, it returns true at last.
